  -- ScriptEvaluator --
  href="#janino-as-a-script-evaluator"           aria-hidden="true">   Janino as a Script           Evaluator                                Analogously to the expression evaluator, a ScriptEvaluator API exists that compiles and processes a Java           "block", i.e. the body of a method. If a return value other than "void" is defined, then the block must           return a value of that type.                                As a special feature, it allows methods to be declared. The place and order of the method declarations is not           relevant.                     Example:              pack
  
